          "Created By:"
        ],
        [
          "International aid worker embraced by the Assamites, you are a new vampire facing a bit of an existential crises about this world you have entered in.",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "Jennifer Wolfe"
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You were born and raised in Los Angeles, in a typical middle class family. You didn't realize how much you had in your life until high school, when you had to do a project on the plight of people in wartorn Darfur. When you went off to college at Berekley you threw yourself into social justice work, and afterwards began working with an aid organization attempting to address issues of displacement and refugees in wartorn areas across the world. You were called in on such a situation in Greece, where the refugees fleeing Syria became such a concern, your organization was sent to help. There you were, a bleeding heart liberal, wanting to save all these lives, and someone else decided to take yours.\n\nYour sire was a refugee himself, an Assamite sent fleeing from his home years ago and who had been hiding in Syria till the political turmoil and those hunting him had sent him fleeing along with the rest. He was impressed with your willingness to help those who needed it and in his admiration decided to make you like him. You aren't sure whether this vampiric existence is good, bad or just there, but it has changed your entire world view. The people you help are just humans for you now, they are food, a resource, one that needs to be protected and nurtured for mutual survivalbility. What is more, there are other vampires, many others, and they have a place in this world as well and always have, playing the politics and making it all run, basically serving as the engine for human civilization. You are still struggling with what that means, whether vampires are a parasite on the world, if they are a neccessary evil to it, or can one side thrive without the other. You wrestle with that.\n\nYou've returned home to LA, to a world that is forever changed. Your sire has informed the others in the city that you are coming home, that you are one of them, and you've been vetted by Salama Shaker, a former clan elder who lived in the city for a time. You are returning to your home radically different, and you aren't sure what that means. You want to ensure that you are still helping the most people, but those people now include the Assamites now - and maybe other vampires? You don't know. What does this mean for the humans you deal with every day? What does this new existence even mean for the calling you thought you had in your life and what your purpose is?  You are young in this world and just learning how dark and terrifying it is. The question is if your ideals can withstand the realities of your new existence."
        ],
        [
          "Sire:",
          "Mordechai ben Yosef",
          "Reference: (If any)",
          "",
          "",
